Sub Desc: #IAdditional #IAttack #I(Ex, #I1 #ICP)#: Gains an additional slam attack.
Sub Desc: #IAdditional #IMovement #I(Ex, #I1 #ICP)#: Gains a new mode of movement (burrow, climb, fly [clumsy], or swim) at a speed equal to its base speed.
Sub Desc: #IConstrict #I(Ex, #I1 #ICP)#: Gains constrict with its slam attacks (the object must have grab before it can take this ability).
Sub Desc: #IFaster #I(Ex, #I1 #ICP)#: One of the object’s movement modes increases by +10 ft.
Sub Desc: #IGrab #I(Ex, #I1 #ICP)#: Gains grab special attack with slam attacks.
Sub Desc: #IMetal #I(Ex, #I2 #ICP)#: The object is made of common metal. Its hardness increases to 10, and it gains a +2 increase to its natural armor bonus. Mithral objects cost 4 CP, and gain hardness 15 plus a +4 increase to natural armor. Adamantine objects cost 6 CP, gain hardness 20, and receive a +6 increase to natural armor.
Sub Desc: #IStone #I(Ex, #I1 #ICP)#: The object is made of stone or crystal. Its hardness increases to 8 and it gains a +1 increase to its natural armor bonus.
Sub Desc: #ITrample #I(Ex, #I2 #ICP)#: The object gains the trample special attack (see page 305 for damage and save DC).
Description: An animated object is not simply one monster, but a whole category. The stats presented here are for a Small animated object (with 1 CP that has not been spent to gain additional abilities), but any object can become animated, most commonly via the spell #Ianimate #Iobjects. Permanent animated objects can be built using the Craft Construct feat (see page 314). Unless an animated object uses a Construction Point to be made of another material, all animated objects are made of wood or material of equivalent hardness. Creating an animated object of a different size than Small can be done simply by adjusting the object’s size (and thus adjusting its Strength, Dexterity, natural armor bonus, and size modifier to attack and AC as detailed on page 296) and Hit Dice.
